## Purpose

This rule ensures ALL code follows Living Design 3.5 (LD 3.5) design system principles: approved design tokens, icon library components, and LD components exclusively. Hard-coded values are strictly prohibited.

---

## 1. Design Token Enforcement

### Rules

- **MUST** use semantic tokens for all colors, spacing, typography, border-radius, elevation, and transitions.
- **MUST NOT** use hard-coded hex colors, RGB values, or color names.
- **MUST NOT** use hard-coded px/rem values for spacing or font sizes.
- **MUST NOT** use primitive tokens directly (use semantic tokens instead).
- **MUST NOT** create new custom CSS variables or design tokens.
- **MUST** use state-specific tokens for interactive elements (hover, focus, pressed, disabled).

### Token Categories

| Category | Token Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Colors | `var(--ld-semantic-color-*)` | `var(--ld-semantic-color-text)` |
| Spacing | `var(--ld-primitive-scale-space-*)` | `var(--ld-primitive-scale-space-200)` (16px) |
| Typography | `var(--ld-semantic-font-*)` | `var(--ld-semantic-font-body-small-size)` |
| Border Radius | `var(--ld-primitive-scale-borderradius-*)` | `var(--ld-primitive-scale-borderradius-100)` (8px) |
| Elevation | `var(--ld-semantic-elevation-*)` | `var(--ld-semantic-elevation-100)` |
| Transitions | `var(--ld-primitive-duration-*)` | `var(--ld-primitive-duration-200)` |
| Icon Sizes | `var(--ld-semantic-scale-icon-*)` | `var(--ld-semantic-scale-icon-small)` (16px) |
| Border Width | `var(--ld-semantic-scale-borderwidth-*)` | `var(--ld-semantic-scale-borderwidth-interactive)` |

### Exceptions (Must Have Inline Comment)

- Exact component height specs from LD 3.5 (e.g., `height: 32px; /* LD 3.5 spec */`)
- Unit-less values (`flex: 1`, `opacity: 0.8`, `z-index: 1000`)
- Transform values (`rotate(45deg)`)

### Do / Don't


/* WRONG */
.card { background: #ffffff; padding: 16px; border-radius: 8px; color: #2e2f32; }

/* CORRECT */
.card {
  background: var(--ld-semantic-color-surface);
  padding: var(--ld-primitive-scale-space-200);
  border-radius: var(--ld-primitive-scale-borderradius-100);
  color: var(--ld-semantic-color-text);
}
```

### Separator Token Rule

All structural borders (card dividers, list separators, table rows, tab underlines) **MUST** use `--ld-semantic-color-separator`. Use specific border tokens only for interactive elements, semantic borders (info/error/warning), and focus outlines.

